snippet.textDisplay:
Taylor doesn’t give himself enough credit, his underestimating himself. His realism shows his capacity to keep on learning and being open minded to learning as a father and adult in general. His exhibited the most maturity as his taken ownership of his mistakes and hardships, its often one of the hardest pill to swallow to admit the wrongs you’ve done or hardship that are generalised/ maybe scrutinised. He was also non judgmental.
The other boys took on a pack mentality weather they realised it or not... it can be both positive but also negative, clear to see it really became US vs HIM in a few instances... grass is greener on out side scenario. You can really hear the statements from the other boys become definitive assertions and you see they amplify by giving similar responses that act as reassurances. You can tell they’re not as secure as they’re portraying especially when you hear ... Me against the world statements but its as though they do feel the pressure of portraying what their perception to be of what “grown man and being a Dad/ family Man/ Man if the house/ provider etc” is.
Good luck to you all. Commend you for having the courage to participate.!Regardless of what stage you are in life know that YOU all have a lot of time ahead... its ok to acknowledge your vulnerabilities as much as your strengths, the two go hand in hand especially in parenting.

snippet.textDisplay: I don’t know why tf they were attacking Josh and Zenon for considering an abortion, their reasonings were logical and made sense. If you don’t have post-secondary it’s really hard to get a job that can pay to support a family and you don’t want to bring a child into the world if you know that you don’t have the resources to give them all of the proper necessities, care, and attention that they deserve. In the end, they ended up keeping the baby and love their children. Therefore, they shouldn’t be shamed for considering an abortion. I personally wouldn’t get one because I don’t think I could handle it emotionally but I support the rights for women to be able to choose what they allow their bodies to go through and I don’t discriminate against the choices they make because it’s their bodies and they know what is best for them because only they know what they are going through and their capabilities.
